<br>
Val <p><img src=http://www.traveling.freehosting.net/valquisssig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugegblix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gegblix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 12:56:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1393.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Apep Speaks</span><hr size=1> Just my own little opinion here but...<br>
<br>
personally I wouldn't try to police any in game concerns unless they had negative consequences either in game or out of game.<br>
<br>
ie...<br>
<br>
Selling characters/equipment for cash has legal implications.  I completely understand not wanting the board to become an auction site.<br>
<br>
Posting of exploits has negative in game consequences.  I would understand if those types of posts were automatically deleted with an explination as to why given to the poster.<br>
<br>
<br>
I really would be very hesatant to &quot;enforce&quot; issues that touch upon &quot;moral&quot; issues in game.  Issues such as selling of gear in game (planar, ST/Primal, etc), scheduling of raids/events, grouping with folks of opposite alignment, roleplay vs non-roleplay guild recruitment messages, class balance questions, etc.<br>
<br>
People are gonna have differing opinions on that kind of stuff and I'm not so sure it's a moderator's place to determine who is right and who is wrong.<br>
<br>
In the case of character sales and exploits, Sony/Verant has already laid down the law, so to speak, and defined what is acceptable and what is not.  Not allowing your board to be used to facilitate people breaking those types of rules is completely understandable.  For all the rest of it, however, I'd say let the discussions take place, let everyone form their own opinion, and just leave it alone.<br>
<br>
As for the selling of Stormhammer loot, I can really see both sides of it.  On the one hand, if Verant was really concerned, all they'd have to do is actually enforce those &quot;pre transfer&quot; checks they supposedly do before someone comes back to a server.  On the other hand, Verant also doesn't activly enforce the &quot;one player per account&quot; rule that precludes character swapping/sales, and yet those kinds of posts *are* deleted because Verant's intent is clear, even if their enforcement is lax.  <br>
<br>
I'm pretty sure Verant's intent about screwing over a server's economy is pretty clear with regards to flooding a younger server with high end items.  There IS a reason why character transfers to non-SH servers are made naked only.  The only question is whether or not Verant cares more about getting $40 a month out of you than they do about the integrity of their game when you're only paying $13.<br>
